text: Sofie Dokter (born 19 December 2002) is a Dutch track and field athlete who is specialized in the heptathlon. Dokter is from Groningen. Dokter represents Netherlands at international competitions. She won the silver medal in the heptathlon at the 2021 European Athletics U20 Championships. As of 2022 she became three times national champion. After becoming 2022 Dutch national champion, she was selected to represent the Netherlands at the 2022 European Athletics Championships where she competed in the heptathlon event. Of the three Dutch women who started, she was the only woman who finished the heptathlon event. Her sister Julia Dokter is also a track and field athlete. ==References== Category:2002 births Category:Dutch athletes Category:Sportspeople from Groningen (province) Category:Living people
